{
  "text": "Concentrated solutions of Lacps1 exhibited the typical color of the blue laccases. In agreement, the absorption spectrum exhibited a peak around 600 nm, indicating the presence of a T1, or blue copper, atom (Figure 4a ). The shoulder seen in the spectrum at around 300 nm suggested the presence of a T3 copper site in the enzyme molecule (Figure 4b ). Highly similar absorption spectra have been obtained for other blue laccases from white-rot fungi [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . ",
